# The Dockerfile never COPY/ADDs anything from this repo -- ORB-SLAM3,
# Pangolin, and depthai-core are all git-cloned from GitHub during the build,
# and every project file reaches the container purely via the runtime `-v`
# mounts in automation.sh, never via the build context. So none of this
# actually affects the build itself -- but keep only workspace/ (the files
# actually used inside the container: workspace/CMakeLists.txt,
# workspace/IMUS_OD_DB.cpp, workspace/datasets/) and patches/ (applied to the
# cloned ORB-SLAM3 fork during the build -- see Dockerfile) un-ignored, in
# case a COPY is ever added later, or something else in the toolchain reads
# the context.
*
!workspace
!workspace/**
!patches
!patches/**
x       